message.body: Bumperstickers in south carolina: 'eat beef: the west wasn't won on salad.'
Is the strong aptitude test worth paying 42 dollars to take?
I have no idea what that is...
My psychologist recommended it to me a year ago. He has a phd, and generally good advice. But the test also seems associated with myers briggs, which i k
now is super out of date, so i don't know.
It's a career test? Yeah the mbti is out of date in the field of psychology but career people use it a lot. 42 seems like a lot...
It is. But if it suggests things i haven't considered it may be worth it. Merr.

True. Yeah it is. In the long run if it is helpful, you will make $42 easily to pay for it. If not then you tried. It seems like you want to take it.
